WEBVTT

00:01.060 --> 00:02.893
<i> - Previously</i>
<i> on "Fantasy Island"...</i>

00:03.004 --> 00:04.895
<i> - Isla.</i>
<i> - A song stuck in your head?</i>

00:05.064 --> 00:06.747
- It's like a siren song.

00:06.841 --> 00:09.066
<i> It's almost like</i>
<i> she's a mermaid.</i>

00:09.084 --> 00:11.251
- Today she asked me
if mermaids exist.

00:11.253 --> 00:13.495
- What did you tell her?
- Stay away from Ruby.

00:13.663 --> 00:15.756
- Everyone and everything
aren't always what they seem.

00:15.758 --> 00:17.499
- Ruby?
- Where have you been?

00:17.501 --> 00:19.351
Did someone tell you
to stay away from me?

00:19.520 --> 00:21.870
- Roarke told me to stay away.
- You lied to me!

00:22.005 --> 00:25.024
You made me think that Isla was
ghosting me when it was you?

00:25.100 --> 00:26.191
- Well, she's dangerous.

00:26.343 --> 00:29.511
- We can be together,
but there's a price.

00:29.530 --> 00:31.030
- I'm in love with her.

00:31.106 --> 00:33.273
- And love can cloud
our vision, Ruby.

00:33.350 --> 00:34.533
Remember life with Mel?

00:34.684 --> 00:36.109
- I don't know
what you're talking about.

00:36.262 --> 00:38.328
- Mel, your husband.

00:40.099 --> 00:43.100
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

00:43.118 --> 00:47.437
[vehicle approaching]

00:47.456 --> 00:54.470
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:55.539 --> 00:56.296
Have you seen Ruby?

00:56.448 --> 00:58.949
- Mm-mm.
No, Ms. Roarke.

00:58.951 --> 01:05.455
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:05.457 --> 01:07.048
- Good morning.

01:07.126 --> 01:08.383
Someone didn't travel light.

01:08.477 --> 01:10.477
- Someone had to make sure
the pens, pads,

01:10.629 --> 01:12.979
water bottles, and stress balls
all got here in one piece.

01:12.981 --> 01:14.464
- Meet Courtney Hobbs.

01:14.558 --> 01:16.149
Courtney, this is Elena Roarke,
your host.

01:16.302 --> 01:17.559
- Welcome to Fantasy Island.

01:17.636 --> 01:19.469
All your coworkers
have safely arrived.

01:19.488 --> 01:21.321
- Oh, well, then
I better get going.

01:21.473 --> 01:23.140
In my job, five minutes
early is ten minutes late.

01:23.142 --> 01:25.158
- Uh, you know
punctuality is important,

01:25.311 --> 01:26.643
but we have plenty
of time to talk

01:26.645 --> 01:28.903
before you have to join them.
- Sure.

01:28.923 --> 01:30.831
- Shall we?

01:30.907 --> 01:34.909
<i> [soft music]</i>

01:34.987 --> 01:37.654
- Ruby?
- I don't know.

01:37.656 --> 01:41.158
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:41.160 --> 01:43.677
- I had my daughter,
Alexis, when I was 17.

01:43.829 --> 01:45.178
I was the same age
as she is now.

01:45.331 --> 01:47.331
She's everything to me.

01:47.349 --> 01:49.166
It's always been
just the two of us.

01:49.168 --> 01:51.668
- Was that hard?
- Beyond hard.

01:51.687 --> 01:54.521
I was a disaster--
no skills, no education.

01:54.673 --> 01:56.340
Sometimes I wonder
how we even made it through.

01:56.433 --> 01:59.267
- T.S. Eliot said,
"Success is relative.

01:59.361 --> 02:02.287
It's what we make of the mess
we have made of things."

02:02.439 --> 02:04.698
- Then I must be
a huge success.

02:04.774 --> 02:06.458
[chuckles]

02:06.535 --> 02:08.869
Except I'm not,
not like I'd like to be.

02:09.021 --> 02:11.964
- From what I understand, you
managed to graduate college,

02:12.115 --> 02:13.132
even got an MBA.

02:13.283 --> 02:15.617
- Night classes,
online courses,

02:15.694 --> 02:18.286
not exactly
Harvard Business School.

02:18.305 --> 02:21.473
- Well, does it have to be?
- It wouldn't hurt.

02:21.550 --> 02:24.309
- Aren't you working
at your dream company?

02:24.311 --> 02:26.979
Seed & Spear--
socially conscious,

02:27.130 --> 02:29.130
environmentally sourced
products.

02:29.208 --> 02:31.391
- I am...
as a receptionist.

02:31.468 --> 02:32.542
- It's a start.

02:32.561 --> 02:35.228
- The founder,
Julia Beryl Thiel...

02:35.305 --> 02:37.214
[sighs]
She's my age.

02:37.232 --> 02:38.565
I studied her
in business school.

02:38.717 --> 02:40.734
- We all have
our own journey, you know.

02:40.810 --> 02:43.162
- Julia is my idol.

02:43.313 --> 02:45.164
- Hi.

02:45.315 --> 02:47.557
Sorry I'm late...again.

02:47.559 --> 02:50.560
- Courtney, this is, uh, Ruby,
my associate.

02:50.579 --> 02:51.670
- Hi.
- [chuckles]

02:51.897 --> 02:53.839
- Courtney and I were
just discussing her job

02:54.066 --> 02:55.156
at Seed & Spear.

02:55.176 --> 02:57.676
- Oh.
"Give light, be light."

02:57.753 --> 02:59.011
Yes, that's their mantra.

02:59.162 --> 03:01.087
I love them.
[chuckles]

03:01.240 --> 03:02.347
- The problem is,
after two years

03:02.499 --> 03:05.184
of taking messages
and fetching coffee,

03:05.260 --> 03:06.852
Julia still doesn't know
who I am.

03:06.929 --> 03:09.021
- Ooh, that cannot feel good.

03:09.097 --> 03:10.522
- It doesn't.

03:10.674 --> 03:12.340
- Courtney,
what can the Island do for you?

03:12.359 --> 03:16.586
- My fantasy is for my boss
to know my name.

03:16.647 --> 03:19.347
I want Julia to see
how much I have to offer.

03:19.441 --> 03:21.182
- And she will.

03:21.260 --> 03:22.367
That's why I have arranged

03:22.519 --> 03:24.428
for Seed & Spear's
company retreat

03:24.446 --> 03:26.279
to happen right here
on the Island.

03:26.432 --> 03:29.433
- Hmm, of course you did.
- [chuckles]

03:29.451 --> 03:32.769
You're gonna take one of these
twice a day.

03:32.788 --> 03:34.671
- What are they?

03:37.109 --> 03:39.051
Caramels?
- Very special ones.

03:39.127 --> 03:40.719
Just enough to last your stay.

03:40.796 --> 03:44.297
But beware--there's no more
of those where they came from.

03:44.374 --> 03:46.708
- Thank you so much for this.

03:46.727 --> 03:48.969
- It's what I do.

03:49.045 --> 03:50.896
You keep an eye on her?
- Yeah.

03:50.973 --> 03:53.565
That's what I do.

03:54.810 --> 03:57.719
Okay, let me take you
to the retreat.

03:57.796 --> 04:00.722
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

04:00.799 --> 04:05.635
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:05.637 --> 04:10.323
And there is great Wi-Fi
for those who need it.

04:10.476 --> 04:12.325
[cell phone vibrating]
And I guess you do.

04:12.402 --> 04:14.086
[laughs]
- Ooh, do you mind?

04:14.162 --> 04:15.645
It's my daughter.
- Oh, no.

04:15.739 --> 04:17.147
[cell phone vibrates, chimes]
- Hey, bug.

04:17.165 --> 04:18.239
<i> - How's paradise?</i>

04:18.259 --> 04:20.742
- It's pretty incredible.

04:20.761 --> 04:22.094
We're heading
to our first event now.

04:22.212 --> 04:25.655
<i> - You got this, lady.</i>
<i> Lipstick-on-teeth check.</i>

04:25.749 --> 04:28.249
- [chuckles]

04:28.327 --> 04:29.509
<i> - All good.</i>
<i> I love you.</i>

04:29.661 --> 04:31.937
- I love you. Bye.
[cell phone chimes]

04:32.088 --> 04:33.680
- Oh, that is so sweet.

04:33.832 --> 04:35.181
- She is.

04:35.258 --> 04:36.942
And spunky.
- [chuckles]

04:37.093 --> 04:40.195
- Do you have children?
- [chuckling]

04:41.690 --> 04:45.008
Uh, you know,
we're not talking about me.

04:45.027 --> 04:47.344
This is your fantasy.

04:47.346 --> 04:49.362
Ready?

04:49.439 --> 04:51.790
<i> [mystical whoosh]</i>
- Mmm.

04:51.867 --> 04:52.958
These are really good.

04:53.109 --> 04:57.111
- Yeah?
Well, you've got this, lady.

04:57.189 --> 04:59.022
- [exhales sharply]

04:59.024 --> 05:01.875
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:02.027 --> 05:03.043
- Hmm.

05:03.119 --> 05:05.304
- [sighs]

05:05.455 --> 05:10.958
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:11.036 --> 05:14.721
[indistinct chatter]

05:14.873 --> 05:20.043
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:20.045 --> 05:22.045
- Oh, finally.

05:22.064 --> 05:23.989
I thought I might have
to do this myself.

05:24.066 --> 05:26.842
- No.
This is my job.

05:26.844 --> 05:28.401
It's all pretty exciting, huh?

05:28.554 --> 05:30.236
<i> - [thinking] Enthusiasm,</i>
<i> but that will pass.</i>

05:30.389 --> 05:33.056
- Sorry, what was that?
- I didn't say anything.

05:33.075 --> 05:35.650
<i> [thinking] Why am I wasting</i>
<i> time on the receptionist?</i>

05:35.727 --> 05:37.410
<i> Next.</i>

05:37.563 --> 05:40.730
<i> - [thinking] He said</i>
<i> it's just a cyst--I'm fine.</i>

05:40.824 --> 05:43.008
<i> - [thinking] Why do I always</i>
<i> push away people who love me?</i>

05:43.159 --> 05:44.250
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Well, there's an itch</i>

05:44.327 --> 05:45.844
<i> I can't scratch in public.</i>

05:45.995 --> 05:47.679
<i> Oh, God, is she looking at me?</i>

05:47.831 --> 05:49.906
- Oh, my God...

05:49.908 --> 05:51.758
I'm a mind reader.

05:51.910 --> 05:54.761
<i> [dreamy music]</i>

05:54.913 --> 06:01.693
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:03.605 --> 06:05.271
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Why is she staring like a fish</i>

06:05.424 --> 06:06.531
<i> with a hook in its mouth.</i>

06:06.683 --> 06:08.141
<i> - [thinking] I'm totally drunk</i>
<i> at 10:00 a.m.</i>

06:08.293 --> 06:09.868
<i> Best retreat ever!</i>

06:10.019 --> 06:12.112
<i> - [thinking] In the end, it</i>
<i> all comes to nothing anyway.</i>

06:12.188 --> 06:13.705
<i> Why do I bother?</i>

06:13.782 --> 06:17.283
<i> - [thinking] I'm so tired</i>
<i> of people ragging on disco.</i>

06:17.360 --> 06:19.119
<i> - [thinking] Did I leave</i>
<i> my curling iron on?</i>

06:19.271 --> 06:20.787
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> There's the receptionist.</i>

06:20.864 --> 06:22.122
Hey.

06:22.198 --> 06:23.940
You filming this
for social media?

06:23.959 --> 06:25.291
- I am.
Courtney.

06:25.444 --> 06:27.052
<i> - [thinking] Isn't this one</i>
<i> an eager beaver?</i>

06:27.129 --> 06:29.446
Julia hates being shot
from the left side,

06:29.539 --> 06:33.392
and high angles
are always appreciated.

06:33.543 --> 06:36.453
<i> [thinking] God, I hope</i>
<i> she can handle this.</i>

06:36.455 --> 06:38.455
I hope you can handle
all of this.

06:38.473 --> 06:42.308
<i> - Welcome to the stage</i>
<i> Julia Beryl Thiel,</i>

06:42.461 --> 06:46.053
<i> founder, CEO of Seed & Spear.</i>

06:46.073 --> 06:49.449
[cheers and applause]

06:51.987 --> 06:53.820
- Thank you, everyone!

06:53.897 --> 06:55.080
It's a joy to see

06:55.231 --> 06:58.475
our entire Seed & Spear
management team together.

06:58.477 --> 07:00.919
Give light...
all: Be light.

07:00.996 --> 07:02.662
- Give light...
all: Be light.

07:02.756 --> 07:04.147
- I love it!

07:04.166 --> 07:07.333
Now, why are you here,
my brilliant illuminators?

07:07.486 --> 07:11.488
To renew, recharge,
and rekindle our passion!

07:11.490 --> 07:12.747
[cheers and applause]

07:12.841 --> 07:15.434
<i> [thinking] You sound shrill.</i>
<i> Lower your voice.</i>

07:15.585 --> 07:16.509
Yes, there will be

07:16.662 --> 07:19.345
team-building exercises
and seminars,

07:19.498 --> 07:22.757
but there will also be
an amazing opportunity

07:22.834 --> 07:24.000
for all of you.

07:24.169 --> 07:27.353
On our last day, each of you
will get two minutes

07:27.506 --> 07:31.933
one-on-one with me to pitch
your game-changing ideas

07:31.952 --> 07:34.453
to expand
our thriving business!

07:34.604 --> 07:37.438
A good idea should sell itself
in 30 seconds.

07:37.458 --> 07:39.532
I'm giving you
90 more than you need.

07:39.685 --> 07:42.035
<i> - [thinking] Oh, man,</i>
<i> I better stop drinking.</i>

07:42.187 --> 07:44.020
<i> - [thinking] Artisanal,</i>
<i> think artisanal.</i>

07:44.022 --> 07:47.691
- Best pitch gets a promotion.
[cheers and applause]

07:47.693 --> 07:52.378
Keep in mind--the worst enemy
to creativity is self-doubt.

07:52.455 --> 07:54.047
<i> [thinking]</i>
<i> Bring it on home, Jules.</i>

07:54.123 --> 07:55.048
And remember...

07:55.124 --> 07:56.308
<i> [thinking] Big finish.</i>

07:56.384 --> 07:59.961
The universe is always working
in your favor!

07:59.980 --> 08:02.689
[cheers and applause]

08:05.134 --> 08:07.877
<i> [thinking]</i>
<i> Sylvia Plath?</i>

08:07.896 --> 08:09.229
<i> What was I thinking?</i>

08:09.381 --> 08:11.156
<i> And I didn't even give her</i>
<i> credit.</i>

08:11.233 --> 08:14.384
Hi. So good to see you.
- So good.

08:14.386 --> 08:16.143
- Mason, so good to see you.

08:16.163 --> 08:18.404
Oh, thank you.
You're so kind.

08:18.406 --> 08:19.906
Hi.
- Hi.

08:20.058 --> 08:21.391
That was incredible.
- Oh.

08:21.409 --> 08:24.819
- And the Sylvia Plath quote
at the end--perfect.

08:24.896 --> 08:26.896
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Maybe it wasn't so bad.</i>

08:26.915 --> 08:28.414
<i> I know this woman's face.</i>

08:28.491 --> 08:30.157
- I'm just in office support,

08:30.177 --> 08:31.343
but I love the company

08:31.494 --> 08:33.236
and everything you did
to make it happen.

08:33.238 --> 08:35.013
- Well, without
dedicated people like you,

08:35.164 --> 08:36.756
Seed & Spear wouldn't exist.

08:36.908 --> 08:38.408
<i> [thinking]</i>
<i> The straps of these sandals</i>

08:38.410 --> 08:40.668
<i> are rubbing my ankles raw.</i>

08:40.746 --> 08:42.020
Hi.
- Incredible.

08:42.097 --> 08:44.689
[indistinct chatter]

08:47.844 --> 08:49.844
- Ruby.

08:49.863 --> 08:52.013
So thank you for coming.

08:52.032 --> 08:53.940
How's it going with our guest?

08:54.017 --> 08:55.275
Off to a good start?

08:55.351 --> 08:58.686
- Oh, definitely.
[chuckles]

08:58.764 --> 09:00.096
We really connected.

09:00.115 --> 09:02.023
- You must remember
what it was like

09:02.100 --> 09:03.708
being a young working mom.

09:03.860 --> 09:06.286
<i> [mystical music]</i>

09:06.362 --> 09:08.621
- Um, you wanted
to speak with me?

09:08.774 --> 09:10.031
- I do.

09:10.050 --> 09:13.051
So this morning
when you weren't at the dock...

09:13.128 --> 09:15.128
were you with Isla?

09:15.280 --> 09:17.238
- Yes. Yeah.
[scoffs]

09:17.315 --> 09:19.724
And before you ask,
I haven't made any decisions

09:19.801 --> 09:21.951
about my future.

09:21.970 --> 09:23.453
- You mean any decisions

09:23.455 --> 09:25.955
about whether you're going
to give up your entire life

09:25.974 --> 09:27.983
to become<i> una sirena?</i>

09:29.795 --> 09:30.902
Hmm.

09:31.129 --> 09:33.238
I'm glad you're taking
your time.

09:35.075 --> 09:37.133
- Sarcasm noted.

09:37.135 --> 09:39.327
Okay, see you later.

09:43.733 --> 09:45.934
- [sighs]

09:45.936 --> 09:49.070
<i> [soft music]</i>

09:49.147 --> 09:50.830
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:50.907 --> 09:52.832
- [exhales deeply]

09:52.909 --> 09:57.170
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:57.246 --> 09:58.838
- Yes?
- Hi.

09:58.915 --> 09:59.989
<i> - [thinking] It's that girl.</i>

10:00.008 --> 10:01.324
- I just wanted you to know

10:01.343 --> 10:04.585
that the video of your speech
is ready to post,

10:04.663 --> 10:07.513
and I thought you could use
these for your sandals.

10:07.666 --> 10:09.849
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Is this woman psychic?</i>

10:10.001 --> 10:11.276
- I know
this might sound weird,

10:11.353 --> 10:13.186
but I have the knockoffs
of your sandals,

10:13.262 --> 10:15.021
and the straps are painful.

10:15.098 --> 10:16.573
That should help a lot.

10:18.267 --> 10:20.768
- What's your name?

10:20.862 --> 10:21.861
- Courtney.

10:22.013 --> 10:23.529
- Courtney...

10:23.682 --> 10:26.333
I'll see you
in a little while, Courtney.

10:28.778 --> 10:32.464
- [squeals, laughing]

10:34.025 --> 10:36.593
- And what are you up to?

10:38.029 --> 10:39.304
- Nothing.

10:39.455 --> 10:42.223
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Said the foxes to the hens.</i>

10:45.887 --> 10:49.230
<i> She is up to something.</i>

10:54.470 --> 10:57.972
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

10:58.049 --> 10:59.157
- Mr. Campos.

10:59.308 --> 11:01.384
Almost time for the fire walk.
- Yes.

11:01.386 --> 11:03.662
Nothing shows more respect
for employees

11:03.813 --> 11:07.666
than making them trudge
across burning-hot coals.

11:07.817 --> 11:11.077
- Uh-huh. Well, I am collecting
everyone's shoes.

11:11.229 --> 11:13.988
May I have your loafers?
- Uh, yeah, I, uh--

11:14.007 --> 11:15.489
I will not be walking
on hot coals.

11:15.567 --> 11:18.234
<i> [thinking]</i>
<i> What is her name? Cassie?</i>

11:18.253 --> 11:20.253
- Courtney,
I was looking for you.

11:20.405 --> 11:22.681
My sandals are a hundred times
more comfortable.

11:22.757 --> 11:23.831
- I'm so glad.

11:23.850 --> 11:26.518
- You're a lifesaver.

11:26.594 --> 11:27.835
- All right.

11:27.913 --> 11:29.503
I've been told the coals

11:29.581 --> 11:31.338
have now exceeded
1,000 degrees,

11:31.416 --> 11:34.341
and the fun can begin
at any time.

11:34.361 --> 11:37.696
<i> - [thinking] For God's sake,</i>
<i> whose idea was this?</i>

11:37.847 --> 11:40.990
Wonderful.
Wonderful.

11:42.260 --> 11:43.593
I prepared some remarks.

11:43.611 --> 11:45.537
Let's do a run-through
before everyone arrives.

11:45.688 --> 11:47.539
- I would love to be
your sounding board.

11:47.766 --> 11:49.040
- Hmm.

11:49.117 --> 11:51.117
Maybe you're asking yourself,

11:51.269 --> 11:54.195
"Why would I ever want to walk
across hot coals?"

11:54.272 --> 11:55.605
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Yes, I'm dying to know.</i>

11:55.623 --> 11:58.775
- Because to reach
one's fullest potential,

11:58.793 --> 12:00.385
we must push past fear.

12:00.536 --> 12:02.462
<i> [thinking]</i>
<i> God, I am terrified.</i>

12:02.538 --> 12:03.537
- I'm with you so far.

12:03.557 --> 12:05.281
- When you make it
to the other side,

12:05.300 --> 12:08.134
you'll receive
something unimaginable--

12:08.286 --> 12:12.063
the knowledge that fear
doesn't have to stop you.

12:12.140 --> 12:14.899
Now, as they say, hold my beer,
and across I go.

12:14.976 --> 12:15.900
What do you think?

12:15.977 --> 12:17.143
- I loved it.

12:17.295 --> 12:20.721
Unflinching, unapologetic,
totally on brand.

12:20.799 --> 12:22.632
- I had goose bumps.

12:22.725 --> 12:25.577
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> I just got a pedicure.</i>

12:25.728 --> 12:29.372
<i> I really wish someone</i>
<i> would get me out of this.</i>

12:32.477 --> 12:33.752
- Julia.
- Hmm?

12:33.979 --> 12:36.829
- There's a situation that
you need to handle right away.

12:36.831 --> 12:38.164
- Oh, no.

12:38.316 --> 12:41.134
<i> [thinking] The universe</i>
<i> does work in my favor.</i>

12:42.095 --> 12:44.670
Apparently I have a crisis.

12:44.823 --> 12:47.323
I have never been more excited
to deal with an emergency.

12:47.342 --> 12:49.416
What's the crisis?
- There isn't one.

12:49.494 --> 12:51.661
I just thought your perfect
pedicure deserved better.

12:51.663 --> 12:54.773
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Well, isn't this one bold.</i>

12:54.924 --> 12:58.167
I don't have to walk on hot
coals to prove I'm fearless.

12:58.186 --> 13:00.111
- Julia, in five minutes,

13:00.263 --> 13:02.113
this beach will be filled
with your acolytes

13:02.190 --> 13:05.116
expecting you to lead them
over the burning coals.

13:05.226 --> 13:06.284
- Luckily, I have

13:06.435 --> 13:09.178
an exceedingly competent
number two.

13:09.197 --> 13:11.272
You're up, Leo.
Give light, be light.

13:11.333 --> 13:13.016
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> This is totally unacceptable!</i>

13:13.018 --> 13:15.502
This is totally unacceptable!

13:17.205 --> 13:19.113
- Where are we going?

13:19.132 --> 13:21.466
- You saved me.
I'm buying you a drink.

13:21.543 --> 13:24.135
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Julia's buying</i> her<i> a drink?</i>

13:24.287 --> 13:25.595
<i> What a kiss-up.</i>

13:29.717 --> 13:32.385
<i> [Latin pop music]</i>

13:32.537 --> 13:36.372
<i> [person singing in Spanish]</i>

13:36.374 --> 13:38.558
- [laughs]
That's how determined I was.

13:38.710 --> 13:41.319
He ducks into the elevator,
I run into the staircase,

13:41.396 --> 13:43.321
and by the time
he gets out on the--

13:43.398 --> 13:45.882
- Seventh floor,
you're in front of his office.

13:45.884 --> 13:47.141
[both laugh]

13:47.160 --> 13:49.160
- Guess I told that one
too many times.

13:49.312 --> 13:51.979
- Mm, as far as I know,
only once--

13:51.998 --> 13:53.998
at the Wharton graduation
four years ago.

13:54.075 --> 13:55.558
I watched it online.

13:55.560 --> 13:57.484
<i> - [thinking] Wow, this girl</i>
<i> does her homework.</i>

13:57.504 --> 13:59.245
I'll tell you something
I didn't tell them.

13:59.397 --> 14:02.398
I closed that initial financing
by lying.

14:02.400 --> 14:05.009
I said I was 21.
I was 20.

14:05.161 --> 14:07.086
[inhales deeply]
I'll never forget.

14:07.238 --> 14:09.438
It was two days
before Christmas.

14:09.440 --> 14:13.500
- When I was 20, I was working
at Filene's Basement.

14:13.578 --> 14:15.836
I didn't even have enough money
for a Christmas tree,

14:15.930 --> 14:18.081
but my boss--he was so great.

14:18.099 --> 14:19.415
He knew I had a three-year-old,

14:19.417 --> 14:21.601
so he let us come in
after hours

14:21.677 --> 14:23.102
so that we could have
Christmas Eve

14:23.179 --> 14:25.271
in front
of the big decorated tree.

14:25.423 --> 14:28.925
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Wow, that's so sad.</i>

14:28.943 --> 14:30.927
- Sorry,
did I bring down the room?

14:30.945 --> 14:32.445
- No.

14:32.597 --> 14:36.875
I mean, yes, it's a little sad
but touching and resourceful.

14:36.951 --> 14:38.525
- I was working
the discount rack,

14:38.545 --> 14:40.545
and you were closing deals
with hedge-fund managers.

14:40.622 --> 14:43.882
<i> - [thinking] And now they</i>
<i> don't even return my calls.</i>

14:43.958 --> 14:45.291
Here's an idea.

14:45.443 --> 14:47.719
I'm hosting a dinner tonight
for department heads.

14:47.946 --> 14:51.055
We're gonna brainstorm, and
we could use some fresh blood.

14:51.207 --> 14:53.908
- I have fresh blood.
- Then it's settled.

14:53.985 --> 14:55.134
Dinner's at 6:00.

14:55.286 --> 14:58.638
But first, more mojitos.

14:58.714 --> 15:00.381
- [laughs]

15:00.458 --> 15:02.959
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:02.977 --> 15:05.219
- Hello.

15:05.238 --> 15:08.055
I heard you wanted to see me.
- I did.

15:08.133 --> 15:09.908
I have a question.

15:09.984 --> 15:11.659
- Oh.

15:13.304 --> 15:15.580
- Why does Elena hate mermaids?

15:15.731 --> 15:17.231
- [sighs]

15:17.325 --> 15:19.918
There is a lot
of history there.

15:20.069 --> 15:22.145
- What kind of history?

15:22.238 --> 15:25.148
- For generations,
there has been a pact

15:25.166 --> 15:27.926
between the mermaids
and the Roarkes.

15:28.153 --> 15:29.410
- Okay.

15:29.487 --> 15:33.414
- Mermaids keep the Island
unknown to outsiders.

15:33.433 --> 15:37.160
In return,
the Island protects them.

15:37.162 --> 15:38.937
- Then what's the problem?

15:39.013 --> 15:40.421
- Many years ago,

15:40.440 --> 15:43.942
there was a mermaid
who seduced a guest

15:44.018 --> 15:46.352
and stole him into the sea.

15:46.429 --> 15:49.188
His family never saw him again.

15:49.340 --> 15:52.951
As far as I know,
he's with them still.

15:53.102 --> 15:54.619
It was a tragedy

15:54.696 --> 15:58.364
that haunted Elena's
great uncle his whole life.

15:58.516 --> 16:01.275
- Well, Isla had no part
in that.

16:01.352 --> 16:03.369
Why should she take the blame?

16:03.521 --> 16:07.298
- Oh, I see.
It's about your friend Isla.

16:08.451 --> 16:12.136
[sighs]
I-it's not a matter of blame.

16:12.213 --> 16:14.197
It's a matter of trust.

16:14.215 --> 16:18.393
In Spanish,
mermaids are<i> sirenas.</i>

16:19.646 --> 16:22.221
- Sirens...

16:22.373 --> 16:24.131
I know.

16:24.209 --> 16:26.876
- Think of it like this.

16:26.894 --> 16:30.822
A shark doesn't always bite...

16:30.898 --> 16:33.533
but it is always a shark.

16:37.071 --> 16:40.573
<i> [soft music]</i>

16:40.649 --> 16:47.547
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:49.825 --> 16:51.083
<i> [line trilling]</i>

16:51.236 --> 16:52.543
[cell phone chimes]
<i> - Hi, Mom.</i>

16:52.620 --> 16:53.511
- Hey, bug.

16:53.738 --> 16:55.738
Give me a pep talk.
I'm so nervous.

16:55.740 --> 16:57.348
Tonight's make or break.

16:57.500 --> 17:00.518
<i> - You are a badass,</i>
<i> boss-babe superwoman.</i>

17:00.669 --> 17:01.668
- I am.

17:01.913 --> 17:03.021
<i> - You're gonna murder</i>
<i> this dinner.</i>

17:03.023 --> 17:04.096
- Murder it.

17:04.249 --> 17:05.931
<i> - I love you.</i>
<i> Call me later.</i>

17:06.008 --> 17:07.750
- I love you.
[cell phone chimes]

17:07.769 --> 17:11.011
[soft music playing]

17:11.089 --> 17:13.756
♪ ♪

17:13.758 --> 17:15.849
<i> [mystical whoosh]</i>

17:15.927 --> 17:21.021
♪ ♪

17:21.041 --> 17:24.876
[music grows louder]

17:24.952 --> 17:26.619
[no audio]

17:26.695 --> 17:30.048
♪ ♪

17:30.275 --> 17:31.957
One is good.
Two is better.

17:32.110 --> 17:35.278
♪ ♪

17:35.280 --> 17:38.281
Give light, be light.

17:38.283 --> 17:40.707
Give light, be light.
Give light, be light.

17:40.785 --> 17:44.970
[indistinct chatter]

17:45.123 --> 17:49.125
- This table
is for directors only.

17:49.127 --> 17:51.385
Shoo.
- Leo...

17:51.404 --> 17:53.237
I invited Courtney to join us.

17:53.464 --> 17:55.907
- Why would you do that?
- Because she's smart.

17:55.983 --> 17:57.483
We could learn a few things
from her.

17:57.635 --> 18:01.579
- Like what.
How to fake an emergency?

18:01.656 --> 18:04.156
<i> [thinking] Did she really</i>
<i> think that wasn't obvious?</i>

18:04.309 --> 18:05.975
I looked you up--

18:05.977 --> 18:07.418
online degree,

18:07.495 --> 18:09.754
only experience
in retail sales.

18:09.831 --> 18:11.497
It was a good effort,

18:11.649 --> 18:16.319
but you have yet to earn
a place at this table.

18:16.321 --> 18:19.413
- I'm honored to be included.
- You should be.

18:19.432 --> 18:22.508
Tonight listen
more than you speak.

18:22.585 --> 18:23.601
- Let's sit.

18:23.752 --> 18:25.919
- You don't want to
embarrass yourself.

18:25.939 --> 18:28.347
<i> [thinking] And that hairdo</i>
<i> isn't helping.</i>

18:28.441 --> 18:31.758
- Everyone,
please welcome Courtney Hobbs.

18:31.778 --> 18:33.594
She might be familiar
to most of you,

18:33.613 --> 18:36.263
and she's made quite
an impression on me this trip.

18:36.357 --> 18:39.191
<i> - [thinking] Let's see</i>
<i> how she handles pressure.</i>

18:39.344 --> 18:40.343
<i> - [thinking] She's got this.</i>

18:40.361 --> 18:42.102
- I knew she looked familiar.

18:42.196 --> 18:45.197
You gave a TED Talk, right?
- It was Big Think.

18:45.274 --> 18:47.274
And it was brilliant.

18:47.352 --> 18:49.276
- No, neither of those things.

18:49.354 --> 18:52.355
- I give up.
Where have we seen you?

18:52.373 --> 18:55.383
- The horseshoe desk
by the front door.

18:56.861 --> 18:58.118
I'm the receptionist.

18:58.138 --> 19:00.454
- Well, um, I always get
my messages,

19:00.473 --> 19:02.214
so you must be good
at what you do.

19:02.367 --> 19:04.642
<i> [thinking] What a joke.</i>
<i> [chuckles]</i>

19:04.793 --> 19:06.126
<i> Well played, Julia.</i>

19:06.128 --> 19:07.311
- We all started somewhere.

19:07.388 --> 19:08.980
<i> [thinking]</i>
<i> Message for the receptionist--</i>

19:09.131 --> 19:10.464
<i> time to get lost.</i>

19:10.483 --> 19:12.966
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> That dress is tragic.</i>

19:13.044 --> 19:16.303
- So I'm dying to know how
everyone's pitches are going?

19:16.381 --> 19:18.230
Jorge, let's start with you.

19:18.383 --> 19:20.491
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> What is her name? Claudia?</i>

19:20.643 --> 19:22.051
<i> - [thinking] I'd rather be</i>
<i> in my room watching HGTV.</i>

19:22.053 --> 19:23.310
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Kendra? Kalisa?</i>

19:23.329 --> 19:24.720
<i> - [thinking] And you're not</i>
<i> exactly starting</i>

19:24.739 --> 19:25.830
<i> ahead of the game.</i>

19:25.981 --> 19:27.239
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Why are people such slobs?</i>

19:27.392 --> 19:29.316
<i> - [thinking] He's definitely</i>
<i> sleeping with her.</i>

19:29.335 --> 19:30.559
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Who's drinking the vermouth?</i>

19:30.578 --> 19:32.152
<i> We're down a bottle</i>
<i> since Tuesday.</i>

19:32.172 --> 19:33.579
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> He can't live forever.</i>

19:33.673 --> 19:35.339
<i> - [thinking] All I really</i>
<i> wanted is a gin and tonic.</i>

19:35.491 --> 19:36.823
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> I hope she doesn't let</i>

19:36.843 --> 19:37.991
<i> these people get to her.</i>

19:38.069 --> 19:39.177
Are you okay?

19:39.328 --> 19:40.753
<i> [thinking]</i>
<i> She's pale as a ghost.</i>

19:40.847 --> 19:41.921
You don't look well.

19:41.997 --> 19:42.847
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> She finally realized</i>

19:42.998 --> 19:44.089
<i> that no one wants her here.</i>

19:44.242 --> 19:45.908
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Don't let them get to you.</i>

19:45.910 --> 19:47.243
<i> - [thinking] Look at her.</i>
<i> Light's on, but nobody's home.</i>

19:47.245 --> 19:48.411
<i> - [thinking] Please cry.</i>

19:48.413 --> 19:49.745
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Thanks a lot, kid.</i>

19:49.764 --> 19:51.189
<i> - [thinking] What is her name?</i>
<i> Caitlin?</i>

19:51.340 --> 19:53.340
- Courtney.
<i> - [thinking] Is she okay?</i>

19:53.418 --> 19:55.251
- My name is Courtney.

19:55.253 --> 19:57.753
<i> - [thinking] I wish</i>
<i> I was livestreaming this.</i>

19:57.772 --> 20:00.364
<i> [laughter]</i>

20:04.353 --> 20:05.611
- You act like you're so nice,
but you're not.

20:05.763 --> 20:07.613
I can hear you, and inside,
you're mean and scared.

20:07.765 --> 20:10.041
You're all scared.
Why can't you just be honest?

20:10.117 --> 20:12.376
And why can't anyone
say what they think?

20:12.528 --> 20:14.620
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Is she off her meds?</i>

20:14.772 --> 20:17.715
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

20:17.866 --> 20:19.608
<i> And there she goes.</i>

20:19.627 --> 20:22.945
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:22.947 --> 20:26.039
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Man, I am famished.</i>

20:26.059 --> 20:28.709
- Take these.
I don't want them anymore.

20:28.786 --> 20:35.650
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:36.885 --> 20:38.811
<i> [mystical whoosh]</i>

20:38.887 --> 20:42.740
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:42.817 --> 20:44.492
Hmm.

20:49.307 --> 20:52.658
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Tequila, 1-1, 2-2,</i>

20:52.810 --> 20:55.311
<i> 3-3, 4-4.</i>

20:55.313 --> 20:58.831
<i> Triple sec,</i>
<i> 1-1, 2-2,</i>

20:58.907 --> 21:01.467
<i> 3-3, 4-4.</i>

21:03.337 --> 21:06.413
<i> - [thinking] Bread, oranges,</i>
<i> sliced turkey, a six pack--</i>

21:06.491 --> 21:09.583
<i> two six packs.</i>

21:09.602 --> 21:11.752
<i> - [thinking] What do you get</i>
<i> a ten-year-old</i>

21:11.771 --> 21:12.845
<i> for their birthday?</i>

21:12.997 --> 21:15.439
<i> They're too old for toys.</i>

21:15.516 --> 21:19.835
<i> - [thinking] Okay, I think</i>
<i> he had the cranberry juice.</i>

21:19.837 --> 21:20.945
<i> Oh, my God, I have to pee.</i>

21:21.096 --> 21:23.990
- Oh, my God,
I'm a mind reader.

21:25.267 --> 21:27.451
[cell phone chimes]

21:30.014 --> 21:32.248
- [sighs]

21:37.188 --> 21:40.631
You wanted to see me?

21:40.783 --> 21:42.591
- Courtney.

21:43.803 --> 21:45.261
Come in.

21:47.031 --> 21:49.307
- I'm so sorry.
I don't know what came over--

21:49.458 --> 21:52.217
- What you said at dinner
was awesome.

21:52.370 --> 21:55.980
- It was?
- Yes, you spoke your truth.

21:56.131 --> 21:59.375
I wish I could be that open
with my feelings.

21:59.393 --> 22:03.546
- So you're not gonna fire me?
- For being authentic? No.

22:03.548 --> 22:07.216
You are exactly the kind
of person I need around me.

22:07.234 --> 22:08.642
You are a bold disrupter,

22:08.661 --> 22:11.329
and disruption
is what will keep us relevant.

22:11.480 --> 22:15.148
<i> [thinking] Now more than ever,</i>
<i> or we are finished.</i>

22:15.226 --> 22:17.226
- I'm so relieved.

22:17.286 --> 22:19.244
- Keep doing what you're doing.

22:19.397 --> 22:22.006
Don't change a thing.
- [chuckles]

22:22.157 --> 22:23.507
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Except for that nail polish,</i>

22:23.659 --> 22:26.344
<i> which is not doing you</i>
<i> any favors.</i>

22:26.495 --> 22:29.088
<i> I'll bring up her hair</i>
<i> another time.</i>

22:29.240 --> 22:31.182
- Julia, I don't mean
to be presumptuous,

22:31.333 --> 22:33.517
but this is me chasing you
to the seventh floor.

22:33.669 --> 22:37.413
I have a pitch, and I think
it could...

22:37.431 --> 22:39.582
revolutionize
the entire company.

22:39.600 --> 22:42.418
<i> - [thinking] Can it keep us</i>
<i> out of bankruptcy?</i>

22:42.420 --> 22:44.028
You don't need to chase me.

22:44.255 --> 22:46.346
I'll have Leo give you
a slot tomorrow.

22:46.424 --> 22:48.199
- [exhales sharply]

22:48.350 --> 22:51.260
You don't know what
this means to me.

22:51.262 --> 22:53.612
- An idea can be a storm.

22:53.689 --> 22:57.023
It can be a whisper
on the wind, or it can be a--

22:57.043 --> 23:00.544
- Seed as fierce as a spear.

23:02.030 --> 23:04.106
I won't let you down.

23:04.125 --> 23:05.624
[chuckles]

23:05.776 --> 23:08.702
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

23:08.779 --> 23:10.779
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:10.781 --> 23:12.781
[door closes]

23:12.800 --> 23:15.968
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:16.120 --> 23:17.377
- Elena.

23:17.397 --> 23:19.288
<i> - [thinking] Dios mío,</i>
<i> he looks so sexy.</i>

23:19.306 --> 23:20.881
<i> I just want to rip</i>
<i> the shirt off him.</i>

23:20.900 --> 23:22.307
- Oh, God.

23:22.460 --> 23:24.568
- Um, what?
Is everything okay?

23:24.720 --> 23:26.553
<i> [thinking] He looks</i>
<i> more than okay from here.</i>

23:26.572 --> 23:29.389
- I made a mistake.
The guest, the receptionist--

23:29.467 --> 23:31.967
<i> - [thinking] Oh, no.</i>
<i> If you slept with her--</i>

23:31.986 --> 23:33.318
Um, what about her?

23:33.395 --> 23:35.913
- [chuckles]
I ran into her tonight.

23:36.064 --> 23:37.306
Actually, she ran into me,

23:37.308 --> 23:40.325
and she gave me
this tin of candies.

23:40.402 --> 23:41.919
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Tell me you didn't eat them.</i>

23:41.996 --> 23:43.737
Uh-huh.
- [sighs]

23:43.814 --> 23:45.589
I should know better than to
eat anything from this island

23:45.741 --> 23:48.592
that I didn't make myself.
<i> - [thinking] Yes, you should.</i>

23:48.744 --> 23:51.429
- But they looked delicious,
so I ate one.

23:51.538 --> 23:53.338
And now I can hear
people's thoughts,

23:53.415 --> 23:55.433
and it's totally
freaking me out.

23:55.509 --> 23:57.176
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Did he hear me say</i>

23:57.328 --> 23:58.769
<i> I want to rip his shirt off?</i>

23:58.921 --> 24:00.420
Yes, just--just take it easy.

24:00.440 --> 24:01.847
You'll be fine by the morning.

24:01.999 --> 24:03.499
- Morning?

24:03.517 --> 24:05.017
That's, like,
eight hours from now.

24:05.169 --> 24:06.277
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> Yes, go now</i>

24:06.428 --> 24:09.004
<i> before you hear something</i>
<i> you shouldn't.</i>

24:09.097 --> 24:11.598
- [chuckles] I should go.
- Yeah, go.

24:11.600 --> 24:13.099
- Yeah.

24:13.177 --> 24:16.287
<i> - [thinking] I love you.</i>

24:17.790 --> 24:20.332
Oh, damn!

24:23.354 --> 24:26.422
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.
No, no, no.

24:29.860 --> 24:33.137
<i> [soft music]</i>

24:33.288 --> 24:35.197
- You see, Elena,
he was far away enough.

24:35.216 --> 24:37.382
Yeah, he probably--
he didn't hear.

24:37.459 --> 24:40.035
Yeah, I'm sure he didn't hear.

24:40.054 --> 24:41.386
No, he totally heard.

24:41.463 --> 24:43.222
There's no way he heard, okay?

24:43.298 --> 24:45.224
- Oh, there you are.

24:45.376 --> 24:47.042
- Ah.
Did something happen?

24:47.135 --> 24:49.153
- I need to get
my caramels back.

24:49.230 --> 24:50.879
- Javier said
that you gave them to him,

24:50.881 --> 24:52.214
so I-I don't understand.

24:52.233 --> 24:54.307
- I was so nervous
that I took two at once.

24:54.385 --> 24:56.885
I figured one was good,
two would be better.

24:56.979 --> 24:58.162
It was a complete catastrophe.

24:58.313 --> 25:00.998
And now
I really need them back.

25:01.149 --> 25:03.483
- Mm, no.
I'm sorry, no.

25:03.503 --> 25:05.077
- No?

25:05.153 --> 25:06.895
- Well, you made the decision
to give them up,

25:06.914 --> 25:08.397
and now this is your new path.

25:08.490 --> 25:11.066
- But Julia gave me a slot
to pitch my idea.

25:11.068 --> 25:12.417
- That's wonderful.

25:12.570 --> 25:14.345
- It's not wonderful
if I humiliate myself.

25:14.496 --> 25:16.347
- Uh, maybe you'll knock it
out of the park.

25:16.423 --> 25:18.349
- I need to know
what Julia is thinking.

25:18.500 --> 25:20.518
That way, if she hates it,
I can pivot.

25:20.594 --> 25:25.264
- Oh, eh, I-I see--
the all-important pivot.

25:25.416 --> 25:28.174
You know, there's something
I want you to see.

25:28.194 --> 25:30.510
- No, I need all the time
I have to prepare.

25:30.588 --> 25:32.655
- Okay, please
just walk that way.

25:34.867 --> 25:36.759
That way.
[chuckles]

25:36.777 --> 25:43.707
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:47.029 --> 25:51.215
[child giggling]

25:59.225 --> 26:03.952
[giggling continues]

26:03.954 --> 26:04.895
- I'm a bunny.

26:05.047 --> 26:06.455
- You're a bunny?
- Yes.

26:06.457 --> 26:08.381
- Like the Easter Bunny?
- No.

26:08.459 --> 26:10.067
- Oh, just a regular bunny.

26:10.218 --> 26:12.294
Santa Claus made
a really fun game for you.

26:12.313 --> 26:13.904
Alexis, do you see
all these presents?

26:13.981 --> 26:15.147
- Mm-hmm.

26:15.299 --> 26:16.740
- Which one do you think
was yours?

26:16.967 --> 26:18.409
- That one.
- [chuckles]

26:18.560 --> 26:20.226
- Why do you think
it's that one?

26:20.304 --> 26:21.637
- It's pink.

26:21.655 --> 26:24.990
- Santa knows that pink
is your favorite color, huh?

26:25.142 --> 26:26.867
Do you want to open it?

26:26.977 --> 26:28.327
Go get it.

26:28.479 --> 26:34.240
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:34.335 --> 26:36.409
What do you think's in here?
- Roller skates?

26:36.487 --> 26:38.578
- Hmm, you think maybe
roller skates.

26:38.598 --> 26:39.988
Is it heavy?

26:40.007 --> 26:41.081
- Yeah.
- [chuckling] Yeah?

26:41.175 --> 26:42.582
What color is this?

26:42.602 --> 26:46.662
Lexie, I was trying so hard
to make Christmas special.

26:46.664 --> 26:47.771
- You did.

26:47.848 --> 26:48.772
- Open it up.

26:48.924 --> 26:51.091
You deserve better.

26:51.168 --> 26:53.669
- Mom, look at me.

26:53.687 --> 26:56.688
- Okay, can you lift it up?
- No, not this me--that me.

26:56.765 --> 26:58.357
- Roller skates!

26:58.509 --> 27:01.601
That's still
my favorite Christmas.

27:01.621 --> 27:03.178
Those are cute.

27:03.180 --> 27:05.105
- Do that again.

27:05.124 --> 27:07.699
- We had nothing, but you gave
me everything--it was magic.

27:07.776 --> 27:11.019
- We were in the lobby
of a closed department store.

27:11.021 --> 27:13.297
- I love them.

27:13.448 --> 27:14.539
Listen to me.

27:14.634 --> 27:17.860
You make magic
with or without magic candies.

27:17.862 --> 27:19.119
You can do this.

27:19.138 --> 27:22.139
- When we get home,
we'll watch "Rudolph," okay?

27:22.290 --> 27:24.883
Until next year,
say bye, Christmas tree.

27:24.960 --> 27:28.036
- Bye, Christmas tree.

27:28.130 --> 27:30.722
<i> [mystical whoosh]</i>

27:30.875 --> 27:37.696
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:44.146 --> 27:47.890
- [exhales deeply]

27:47.892 --> 27:49.625
- Nailed it!

27:54.081 --> 27:56.215
- I can wait.

28:02.423 --> 28:03.663
- Oh, yay.

28:03.849 --> 28:07.167
Courtney, this afternoon
has been a total snooze fest.

28:07.186 --> 28:10.020
Are you ready to blow us away?
- That's the plan.

28:10.097 --> 28:12.356
- Just don't pitch
artisanal manure.

28:12.507 --> 28:14.416
- [sighs]
- It's not a thing.

28:14.435 --> 28:15.417
- Mm, got it.

28:15.510 --> 28:18.487
Ixnay
on the artisanal anure-may.

28:23.869 --> 28:25.369
Um...

28:25.596 --> 28:29.355
for most of my life, I thought
my dreams couldn't come true.

28:29.450 --> 28:31.950
But then I read an article
about you, Julia,

28:32.102 --> 28:33.377
and your belief in yourself

28:33.528 --> 28:36.438
and your vision
for Seed & Spear inspired me.

28:36.440 --> 28:39.049
I've been at the company
for two years now,

28:39.201 --> 28:42.794
and I am certain
that Seed & Spear's future

28:42.947 --> 28:44.963
is not in another $100 candle

28:45.115 --> 28:49.727
or, as Leo said,
a bag of artisanal manure.

28:49.803 --> 28:52.788
The way forward is to go back

28:52.806 --> 28:54.973
to the company's roots--

28:55.125 --> 28:57.383
the farm box.

28:57.461 --> 29:00.479
But make it accessible for all.

29:00.573 --> 29:04.224
My idea is to create
an affordable version

29:04.301 --> 29:05.634
with an associated brand

29:05.652 --> 29:08.320
that won't impact the
parent company's bottom line.

29:08.396 --> 29:11.081
In time, we'll create jobs,
reduce waste,

29:11.158 --> 29:12.398
and improve the diets

29:12.418 --> 29:14.234
of an ever-increasing number
of people,

29:14.328 --> 29:16.979
people like me
who want to feed their kids

29:16.997 --> 29:21.258
healthy, accessible,
affordable food.

29:21.409 --> 29:25.821
- And you've run the numbers?
- It's all in here.

29:25.823 --> 29:27.506
By my conservative projections,

29:27.582 --> 29:30.325
profits could increase 30%
in the next 5 years.

29:30.344 --> 29:32.418
- And the initial investment?
- Minimal.

29:32.438 --> 29:36.164
The infrastructure's
already in place.

29:36.166 --> 29:37.649
- Okay, thank you.

29:41.263 --> 29:43.489
- Uh, you can go now.

29:51.106 --> 29:53.015
- I spoke to Segundo.

29:53.017 --> 29:55.209
- How is the old man?

29:56.295 --> 29:57.610
- He told me a story

29:57.630 --> 30:01.706
about a feud between
the Roarkes and the mermaids.

30:01.783 --> 30:03.041
Why didn't you tell me?

30:03.135 --> 30:06.119
- Our relationship
is about you and me,

30:06.138 --> 30:07.954
not about anybody else.

30:08.032 --> 30:14.036
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:14.054 --> 30:16.796
- Did your people steal
a guest?

30:16.816 --> 30:19.650
- No one was stolen.

30:19.801 --> 30:24.229
There was a guest who fell
in love with one of us.

30:24.381 --> 30:28.492
He chose to join us,
just like I hope you will.

30:30.237 --> 30:33.479
- Is he still with you?
- He is.

30:33.557 --> 30:36.959
Perhaps someday
you'll meet him.

30:38.078 --> 30:39.628
- Perhaps.

30:46.420 --> 30:49.921
- Take all the time you need.

30:49.998 --> 30:52.757
- [breathes deeply]

30:52.834 --> 30:55.668
[chuckles]

30:55.746 --> 30:59.081
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:59.099 --> 31:02.192
- [breathing shakily]

31:05.013 --> 31:08.115
[knock at door]

31:09.368 --> 31:13.645
Julia, what a nice surprise.
Please come on in.

31:13.797 --> 31:15.113
- So...

31:15.265 --> 31:16.448
Courtney, I'm going to make

31:16.600 --> 31:18.542
an official announcement
tomorrow,

31:18.693 --> 31:21.103
but I wanted to talk
to you first.

31:21.105 --> 31:22.437
- I'm all ears.

31:22.456 --> 31:24.439
- I loved your pitch.
I really did--

31:24.441 --> 31:26.775
thought-provoking,
well-considered.

31:26.793 --> 31:28.443
- Okay.

31:28.445 --> 31:30.629
- But I'm going to let you go.

31:30.705 --> 31:33.056
- Let me--

31:33.208 --> 31:36.635
What?
- Our visions don't align.

31:36.711 --> 31:38.270
- But they do.

31:39.806 --> 31:42.048
- The Julia Beryl Thiel
that you admire

31:42.067 --> 31:43.808
is a marketing tool

31:43.885 --> 31:46.052
to sell bespoke washcloths

31:46.130 --> 31:48.238
and ethically sourced
pine cones

31:48.390 --> 31:51.299
to rich people with more money
than common sense.

31:51.318 --> 31:53.818
- I don't understand.

31:53.895 --> 31:57.322
- You're an idealist, Courtney.

31:57.474 --> 31:59.232
- So are you.

31:59.251 --> 32:00.325
- No.

32:00.477 --> 32:01.734
I'm a pragmatist.

32:01.754 --> 32:05.255
Ultimately, my top priority
is shareholder value.

32:05.407 --> 32:08.650
Seed & Spear is
a high-end lifestyle brand.

32:08.669 --> 32:12.912
It's not a "save the world,
feed the people" brand.

32:12.932 --> 32:15.599
- It could be both.

32:15.676 --> 32:17.476
- But it won't be.

32:20.773 --> 32:22.981
- What about
"give light, be light"?

32:25.927 --> 32:27.185
- Courtney...

32:27.279 --> 32:29.780
I don't want to be
the one responsible

32:29.931 --> 32:33.008
for dimming your light.

32:33.026 --> 32:34.785
Seed & Spear isn't the place
for you.

32:34.861 --> 32:38.697
If you need a recommendation,
don't hesitate to reach out.

32:38.849 --> 32:41.107
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:41.185 --> 32:43.460
And, Courtney...

32:43.611 --> 32:48.690
the universe is always working
in your favor.

32:48.692 --> 32:51.784
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:51.862 --> 32:55.430
[door opens, closes]

32:58.869 --> 33:01.369
[knock at door]
- Courtney?

33:01.371 --> 33:03.629
Courtney?
[knocking continues]

33:03.649 --> 33:05.607
- [sighs]

33:10.063 --> 33:13.139
[door closes]

33:13.158 --> 33:15.217
- I know it's tempting
to see this as a failure.

33:15.235 --> 33:17.310
- That's because
it is a failure.

33:17.329 --> 33:19.479
I'm an idealistic,
tone-deaf idiot

33:19.498 --> 33:22.815
with terrible ideas
and bad hair.

33:22.893 --> 33:26.628
- I think your hair is lovely.

33:28.398 --> 33:30.565
You know, sometimes
the wrong door has to close

33:30.584 --> 33:33.084
so we can move
through the right one.

33:33.237 --> 33:35.828
- How can I tell Alexis
that I lost my job

33:35.906 --> 33:37.405
and that our future is ruined?

33:37.424 --> 33:40.017
- One person didn't like
your pitch,

33:40.168 --> 33:42.168
and now your entire
future is ruined?

33:42.246 --> 33:44.021
- Well, it certainly seems
a lot more bleak

33:44.097 --> 33:46.857
than it did 24 hours ago.

33:47.008 --> 33:48.433
I feel lost.

33:48.585 --> 33:52.087
- If Alexis had
the same experience,

33:52.089 --> 33:54.013
what would you tell her?

33:54.033 --> 33:56.274
- I would tell her
to believe in herself,

33:56.426 --> 33:58.610
hold her head up high,
and move on with dignity.

33:58.612 --> 34:02.097
- Your daughter is lucky
to have such a wise mom.

34:02.099 --> 34:04.541
And you can't stay
under the covers forever.

34:04.543 --> 34:07.269
It's time to believe
in yourself,

34:07.271 --> 34:10.772
hold your head high,
and move on with dignity.

34:10.791 --> 34:13.792
<i> [soft music]</i>

34:13.868 --> 34:18.947
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:18.965 --> 34:20.891
[chuckles]

34:20.967 --> 34:28.231
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:30.143 --> 34:31.217
- Hey.

34:31.295 --> 34:33.052
What brings you
to my neck of the woods?

34:33.130 --> 34:34.720
- I'm worried about Ruby.

34:34.798 --> 34:35.980
- Elena--

34:36.133 --> 34:38.057
- Javier,
I think she's in danger.

34:38.135 --> 34:41.303
- What, from Isla?

34:41.396 --> 34:43.563
- Isla is not
who Ruby thinks she is.

34:43.582 --> 34:46.583
And if we sit back
and we do nothing,

34:46.734 --> 34:49.661
she very well may take Ruby
to the ocean with her...

34:49.737 --> 34:50.736
forever.

34:50.756 --> 34:52.255
- Okay, I hear you, okay?

34:52.332 --> 34:54.332
But if that's what Ruby wants,
isn't that her decision?

34:54.409 --> 34:56.167
- Only if she's doing it
with a sound mind.

34:56.320 --> 34:58.153
- What do you mean?

34:58.171 --> 35:01.673
- I think Isla's stealing
her memories.

35:01.749 --> 35:03.249
And I...

35:03.327 --> 35:05.685
I need to know for sure.

35:07.106 --> 35:10.014
- [sighs]
That's where I come in.

35:10.167 --> 35:11.516
- She trusts you.

35:11.668 --> 35:14.669
You know, she'll open up to you
if she can.

35:14.688 --> 35:17.781
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:17.858 --> 35:20.342
Thank you.

35:20.344 --> 35:27.015
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:27.017 --> 35:30.168
- [sighs]
[knock at door]

35:33.132 --> 35:34.873
- Heading home?
- No.

35:34.967 --> 35:36.541
I thought I'd spend a year
traveling the world

35:36.693 --> 35:38.710
and then find
another low-paying job.

35:38.804 --> 35:41.138
- Mm, yeah, heard you crapped
out on your pitch.

35:41.214 --> 35:42.455
Honestly, I was amazed

35:42.474 --> 35:44.199
you weren't fired
after that dinner.

35:44.201 --> 35:46.810
- Why are you here, Mason?

35:46.887 --> 35:48.703
- Company property.

35:48.722 --> 35:51.314
Unless you're planning
on taking those with you.

35:51.541 --> 35:54.133
- Yeah, I was about to steal
a box of stress balls,

35:54.153 --> 35:56.653
'cause that would be
the answer to all my problems.

35:56.804 --> 35:58.229
- [chuckles]

35:58.382 --> 36:00.806
Julia wants you to leave it all
in her suite.

36:00.884 --> 36:02.550
Here's the key.

36:02.552 --> 36:04.828
[sighs]
Don't take this too hard, huh?

36:04.979 --> 36:07.055
It's all a learning experience,

36:07.057 --> 36:09.391
and you learned a lot.

36:09.393 --> 36:12.744
- Yeah, I learned you suck.

36:12.896 --> 36:15.563
<i> [upbeat tropical music]</i>

36:15.565 --> 36:16.673
[sighs]

36:16.824 --> 36:21.178
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:21.329 --> 36:23.254
- Oh, somebody brought
their appetite.

36:23.407 --> 36:26.090
- If the sun has risen,
I'm ravenous.

36:26.243 --> 36:27.425
<i> - [thinking]</i>
<i> I may have to slip</i>

36:27.519 --> 36:29.577
<i> those salt and pepper shakers</i>
<i> into my luggage.</i>

36:29.579 --> 36:32.747
<i> - [thinking] It's not a lump.</i>
<i> It's just a cyst.</i>

36:32.749 --> 36:35.525
<i> [mystical music]</i>

36:35.602 --> 36:38.920
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:38.939 --> 36:41.031
- So...

36:41.107 --> 36:42.699
what's new?

36:42.776 --> 36:49.664
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:09.061 --> 37:12.354
[bowls humming]

37:17.569 --> 37:20.219
[gong resounding]

37:20.297 --> 37:22.797
[indistinct chatter]

37:22.799 --> 37:25.149
- Courtney.

37:25.302 --> 37:27.911
- Give light, be light, my ass!

37:28.062 --> 37:30.062
[indistinct chatter]

37:30.082 --> 37:33.291
You stole my idea.
- [gasps]

37:36.646 --> 37:39.981
- You stole my idea!
Don't deny it!

37:40.000 --> 37:41.316
- Okay.

37:41.334 --> 37:44.094
Okay, let's all take a breath.

37:44.287 --> 37:46.154
Courtney here
is understandably upset

37:46.156 --> 37:47.747
because she was just let go.

37:47.766 --> 37:50.558
- I wasn't let go.
You fired me.

37:52.587 --> 37:54.437
- How about we discuss
this privately?

37:54.514 --> 37:55.605
- I think here's good.

37:55.774 --> 38:00.184
Julia Beryl Thiel is not
who she pretends to be.

38:00.337 --> 38:01.778
Seed & Spear is in trouble.

38:01.929 --> 38:05.023
Hedge-fund managers
won't even return her calls.

38:05.175 --> 38:07.450
- How would you know that?

38:07.602 --> 38:08.618
Leo?

38:08.770 --> 38:10.361
- I didn't tell her,

38:10.363 --> 38:12.289
but she is the receptionist.

38:12.365 --> 38:15.199
- Was, until she stole my idea
to save the company.

38:15.352 --> 38:16.518
- Don't be ridiculous.

38:16.520 --> 38:19.020
I came up
with a brilliant new direction

38:19.022 --> 38:20.188
for Seed & Spear.

38:20.190 --> 38:22.190
My idea, not hers.

38:22.192 --> 38:23.616
- You came up
with marketing ideas,

38:23.635 --> 38:26.786
and you're already contacting
potential distributors.

38:26.863 --> 38:28.029
Just admit it, Julia.

38:28.031 --> 38:29.121
It's all in here.

38:29.199 --> 38:31.624
[book thuds]

38:31.701 --> 38:33.351
- You broke into my suite.

38:33.428 --> 38:34.702
- You wanted
the stress balls back.

38:34.721 --> 38:35.961
- What stress balls?

38:35.981 --> 38:37.981
- It's what he said
when he gave me your key.

38:38.132 --> 38:39.557
- You gave her my key?

38:39.634 --> 38:42.226
- To be fair, I gave him
the key, Julia,

38:42.321 --> 38:45.688
and I told him
to give it to her.

38:45.765 --> 38:47.215
- Why would you do that?

38:47.233 --> 38:48.550
- Because you're a liar.

38:48.568 --> 38:51.143
[people gasp,
chattering in disbelief]

38:51.221 --> 38:53.163
And I'm not gonna
let you be a thief.

38:53.314 --> 38:56.741
- So now you're the arbiter
of what's right and fair?

38:56.893 --> 38:58.893
- I'm done enabling you.

38:58.895 --> 39:00.295
You're on your own.

39:01.731 --> 39:03.340
- If you're in the market
for new partners,

39:03.491 --> 39:05.157
I know someone
who just became available,

39:05.177 --> 39:06.509
and she has great ideas.

39:06.661 --> 39:07.902
- Do you, now?

39:08.088 --> 39:11.181
- You don't have a clue
as to what it takes, Courtney.

39:11.257 --> 39:14.684
- Maybe, maybe not.

39:14.836 --> 39:17.837
But she'll have my help.

39:17.914 --> 39:19.914
- Are you kidding?

39:19.933 --> 39:21.749
- Hell, yeah.

39:21.751 --> 39:24.361
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

39:24.437 --> 39:26.178
What's the worst
that could happen?

39:26.198 --> 39:27.438
- Well, you could fail

39:27.515 --> 39:29.273
and lose a lot
of investor money

39:29.426 --> 39:31.275
and be right back
where you started.

39:31.428 --> 39:34.112
- No way. I'm a badass,
boss-babe superwoman.

39:34.188 --> 39:36.373
- That's the attitude.

39:36.524 --> 39:38.691
- Uh, Julia...

39:38.768 --> 39:42.937
remember he universe is
always working in your favor.

39:42.956 --> 39:49.052
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:49.129 --> 39:51.796
- Leo was dead weight.

39:51.873 --> 39:55.875
- Get...away...from me.

39:55.894 --> 40:03.191
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:10.575 --> 40:13.993
- Thank you for being on time.
- No problem.

40:17.916 --> 40:19.082
- Good morning.

40:19.233 --> 40:22.252
- I hope you can handle
an extra passenger.

40:22.403 --> 40:25.237
I am no longer welcome
on the corporate jet.

40:25.315 --> 40:26.998
- Of course.
[chuckles]

40:27.074 --> 40:28.149
- Thank you.
- Perfect.

40:28.151 --> 40:30.001
We have so many things
to discuss

40:30.153 --> 40:32.503
about our new company.
- Yes, we do.

40:32.656 --> 40:33.746
- Thank you.

40:33.990 --> 40:37.583
- Hmm, well, I am sure
it will be a huge success.

40:37.661 --> 40:39.227
- No doubt.

40:40.922 --> 40:42.922
- Will you check that?
- Yes, sir.

40:42.941 --> 40:44.691
- Excuse me.

40:47.854 --> 40:49.112
- Well?

40:49.263 --> 40:51.839
- So I listened
to Ruby's thoughts.

40:51.858 --> 40:54.175
- And?
- It's all gone.

40:54.194 --> 40:55.768
- What do you mean?

40:55.787 --> 40:58.103
- As far as I can tell, she
remembers nothing of her life

